  "body": "Hi All,\r\n\r\nI am using npx hardhat run to run a CLI script that has its own set of arguments\r\n\r\nI know that I can use `npx hardhat run ./path/to/script` but I want to be able to do it so that I can also pass arguments to the script itself, like so:\r\n\r\n`npx hardhat run src/CLI.js -arg1ForCLI.js xxx`\r\n\r\nif I do this I will get the following error:\r\n\r\n`Error HH308: Unrecognized positional argument`\r\n\r\nIs there a way round this? Thank you for your time and for building an excellent tool for the community! ",
